# What measures can be taken to ensure that further attacks of the Polish missile attack in Bali are prevented?

## Summary
In response to the missile strike in Poland near its border with Ukraine that killed two people, Indonesian President Joko Widodo called for all parties to remain calm and not escalate tensions <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. President Biden has also said that preliminary information suggests it is unlikely the missile was fired from Russia <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. The US National Security Council has declined to comment and is supporting Poland's ongoing investigation <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>. NATO and the European Union are also likely to have repercussions for the attack <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. It is important for global leaders, such as President Biden, to ensure there is clear communication between all countries to prevent any further haphazard responses that could lead to further escalation <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>.

